Version 1.8 of 'almclk' is installed.

This version allows the tool to work on Solaris.

Synopsis of tool:
'Almclk' allows you to set an alarm at your terminal.
It will send a message to your terminal when the alarm
goes off.  If you are not logged in at the time, an
e-mail message will be sent to you.  You can customize
the alarm by specifying a message of your choice.  Also,
a 5-minute warning is sent to your terminal.  If you
wish to kill the alarm, a script is created for you
to do so.  The tool can be invoked with or without
arguments.  Necessary information is prompted for.

See "toolman almclk" for more information.

Provider:
